    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-24T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="419"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d419">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.796/84: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-24T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 24, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Department’s No. 13, February 18, 8 p.m. Memorandum asking whether Bolivian
                    Government would agree in principle to consider plan for reorganization of
                    L.A.B. was presented to Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="6" xml:id="d419fn1"
                        >Alberto Ostria Gutiérrez.</note> on February 20. He expressed personal
                    agreement and said he would take matter up at Cabinet meeting and give me
                    definite reply. He did not mention proposed approach to the Department by the
                    Bolivian Minister in Washington<note n="7" xml:id="d419fn2">Luis Fernando
                        Guachalla.</note> for assistance in reorganization of L.A.B. stated by
                    Minister of Finance<note n="8" xml:id="d419fn3">Joaquín Espada.</note> to have
                    been decided upon as reported in my despatch 648, February 13.<note n="9"
                        xml:id="d419fn4">Not printed.</note> Carnival holidays and departure of
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs from La Paz will probably delay answer for some
                    time. Will report further after return of Minister for Foreign Affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
